 a team player who thrives working with others. This position reports to the VP, Enterprise Solutions. Responsibilities Direct and manage client engagements across all stakeholders from the initial idea / formulation phase through to successful final delivery Work with clients to gather concrete business requirements and translate those into internal functional specifications and ultimately deliverable solutions Provide subject matter expertise on financial products, capital markets, and associated workflows Collaborate with engineering teams to develop solutions built on Axoni\u2019s software and guide the development of the product Ensure effective communication with key customer stakeholders and internal management Oversee the project management of internal and external project resources and managing the overall project budget Manage other Enterprise Solutions team members to effectively execute initiativesSkills Required Experience leading large-scale financial system vendor implementations in exchanges / CCPs, investment banks, and/or asset managers 10+ years of experience within a financial technology firm, management consulting, professional services, and/or capital markets operations Significant client facing experience and strong communication and stakeholder management skills Experience and deep domain knowledge across multiple institutional asset classes; post-trade derivatives preferred Experience in working with multiple cross-functional teams across a dynamic environment to deliver successful implementations of capital markets (or equivalent complexity) technology Proven capability and experience developing models and presentations suitable for clients and senior management Basic understanding of DLT and the value proposition of the technology Fundamental technical proficiency preferred (e.g. experience with scripting languages and/or familiarity with basic computer science / programming concepts) Proven problem-solving and analytical skills Excellent 